The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Thursday, December 29, 2005 

 Chennai: World champion Pankaj Advani and former Asian champion Alok Kumar have been given pride of place in the billiards and snooker sections of the 72nd National Championships to be held here from Monday to January 18.

 Top rung cueists like former world champion (billiards) Geet Sethi, Yasin Merchant, Ashok Shandilya, Devendra Joshi and Rafat Habib will be seen in action at the national championship, besides Vidya Pillai and Anuja Thakur, defending ladies champions in snooker and billiards respectively.

 Sub-junior (under-17) billiards and snooker is being introduced for the first time at the national event. The 30th junior (billiards and snooker) championships would also be held concurrently.

 New Delhi: Indian Airlines defeated Punjab Police 2-1 to advance to the semi-finals of the 42nd Nehru Hockey here on Wednesday. In another quarter final, Namdhari XI booked the semi-final berth ahead of Bharat Petroleum with an identical 2-1 victory at the Shivaji Stadium.

 Gagan Ajit Singh opened the account for Punjab Police with a superb goal in the ninth minute but Dhanraj Pillay scored the equaliser for Airlines in the 11th minute. Birendra Lakra scored just before the lemon break to make it 2-1 for Indian Airlines.

 Namdhari XI scored through Joga Singh (10th) and Anmolak Singh (38th) while international Len Aiyappa (15th) struck for Bharat Petroleum. 

 New Delhi: Ace shooters Anjali Bhagwat and Suma Shirur failed to hold on to their place for the air rifle event at the Melbourne Commonwealth Games to be held in March next year. Young guns Avneet Kaur Sidhu and Tejaswini Sawant have been included instead in the 36-member squad announced by the National Rifle Association of India here on Wednesday.

 Lisbon: Brazilian winger Gustavo Manduca has joined Benfica from Maritimo on a four-and-a-half-year contract, the Portuguese champions said on Wednesday.

 No financial details of the deal were given but Portuguese media reported that Benfica would pay around half a million euros to the Madeira Island club. 

 Bucharest: Spaniard Esteban Vigo has signed a six-month contract to coach Romanian league leaders Dinamo Bucharest, a club official said on Wednesday.

 Former coach Ioan Andone surprisingly resigned this month to join Omonia Nicosia of Cyprus. ?Esteban Vigo will coach Dinamo for the next six months,? executive president Ioan Becali said.

 Athens: Greece captain Theodoros Zagorakis has been offered a job with the national team should he decide to quit playing.

 The 34-year-old, who led Greece to victory in Euro 2004, plays for PAOK Salonika but has indicated that he may quit soon.

